getMatchingPresetNodes() - Method in class nusri.fyp.demo.entity.StateMachineLog
Retrieves the matching PresetNode objects based on the observations.
The method returns a map of timestamps to the corresponding PresetNode objects.
A matching logic is applied where the AbstractActionObservation.s() method's result is checked against the actions in the PresetNode list.
The match is considered if the action from the observation matches the action in the node either as a prefix or suffix, or exactly.
getMatchingPresetNodes(boolean) - Method in class nusri.fyp.demo.entity.StateMachineLog
Retrieves the matching PresetNode objects based on the observations.
The method returns a map of timestamps to the corresponding PresetNode objects.
The match logic follows the same as StateMachineLog.getMatchingPresetNodes(), but with an option to add a "transfer" action if no observations exist.
A matching logic is applied where the AbstractActionObservation.s() method's result is checked against the actions in the PresetNode list.
The match is considered if the action from the observation matches the action in the node either as a prefix or suffix, or exactly.

Simulates the execution of the state machine based on the observations in the current log entry.
If Quota is enabled, it performs real-time updates; if Quota is disabled, it performs SegmentPartitionByDP inference.
The final sequence of steps (nodes) is returned as a timeline.
